The invention will be better understood by way of the following description of a preferred embodiment of the invention with reference to the appended drawings, in which:


FIG. 1 illustrates a beam intensity distribution of a single beam with Gaussian intensity distribution (G-solid line) and a specially deformed beam (D-dashed line);


FIG. 2 illustrates the interaction between a transparent and isotropic object (AO) and a light beam having a wave vector (K) with an electric field vector component E causing a rotation in the anisotropic object with a rotation rate R;


FIG. 3 is a schematic diagram illustrating the apparatus according to the preferred embodiment; and


FIG. 4 illustrates schematically an apparatus according to an alternative embodiment in which spatial separation of two polarizations of the light with their further recombination is provided to obtain two co-propagating non-coherent beams forming an electromagnetic field with varied angular momentum while keeping at the same time its azimuthal symmetry.
